BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7xSBcZkyGQyEPy2G9fM9y
SUMMARY:Pine Box Beer Can Derby
DTSTAMP:20260407T043746Z
DTSTART:20250510T220000Z
DESCRIPTION:The race is on! Come &amp\; try your luck racing cans cub scout
	 style down the tracks to beer glory. Join us at 3pm to purchase a beer\, 
	canned of course\, &amp\; a race kit. We’ll race in heats starting at 5pm 
	w/ prizes for 1st\, 2nd\, &amp\; 3rd + most attractive car! Tools will be 
	provided. Cub scout gear encouraged! See you at the starting line.3pm to 5
	pm - Build Time 5pm - RACE TIME!!ALL CARS MUST PASS INSPECTION TO QUALIFY 
	FOR THE RACE Following are the inspection points 1. The can weight shall n
	ot exceed 5.0 ounces. The official race scale shall be considered final. 2
	. The overall length of the can shall not exceed 7 inches. 3. The overall 
	width of the can shall not exceed 2 ¾ inches. 4. The can must have 1 ¾” cl
	earance between the wheels. 5. The can must have 3/8” clearance underneath
	 the body. 6. The can may be shaped any way that is desired. 7. The can mu
	st be freewheeling\, with no starting devices. 8. You must use official Pi
	ne Box Wheels and Axles\, YOUR CAN CAR MUST BE BUILT ON SITE.Each can must
	 pass inspection by the official inspection committee  before it will be a
	llowed to compete. The Inspection Committee has the  responsibility to dis
	qualify those cans that do not meet these  specifications.Hosted by New Be
	lgium Brewing\n\nFrom Seattle Beer Week
LOCATION:Location ID: m7279q0m
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:beer-week
CATEGORIES:Seattle Beer Week
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
